
# Commit Message Template for CallScan (Backend)
#
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
#
# Types:
#   feat     → A new feature
#   fix      → A bug fix
#   refactor → Code change that doesn't add or fix, just restructures
#   test     → Adding or updating tests
#   docs     → Documentation changes
#   chore    → Maintenance work (deps, configs, etc.)
#
# Scopes:
#   upload, api, crewai, sentiment, compliance, summary, risk, report, rules
#
# Example:
#   feat(upload): add file validation for audio types
#   fix(api): handle null transcript in POST /analyze
#   refactor(crewai): move agents to separate module
#
# --------------------------------------------------
<type>(<scope>): <short, imperative summary>

# Optional body:
# Use the body to explain what and why, not how.
# Wrap at 72 characters if needed.
#
# For example:
# This commit adds validation for file types on the upload endpoint.
# It supports .mp3 and .wav only, and returns 400 for invalid files.
#
# Footer (optional for breaking changes or linked issues):
# BREAKING CHANGE: new auth required for /analyze
# Closes #14
